<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04157</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING SECTIONS 4, 5, 20, 22, 27, 28, 34, 40, 50, 73, 112, 117, 204, 222, 237, 237-A, 255, 256, 257, 258, 261, 263, 264, 266, 275, 290, 291, 292 AND ADDING NEW SECTIONS 6-A, 282-A, 293, 294, 295, 296, 297, 298, 299, 300, 301, 302, 303, 304, 305, 306, 307, 308, 309, 310,  311, 312, 313, 314, 315 AND 316 ALL UNDER THE NATIONAL INTERNAL REVENUE CODE OF 1997, AS AMENDED, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Amending Sections 4, 5, 20, 22, 27, 28, 34, 40, 50, 73, 112, 117, 204, 222, 237, 237-a, 255, 256, 257, 258, 261, 263, 264, 266, 275, 290, 291, 292 And Adding New Sections 6-a, 282-a, 293, 294, 294-a, 295, 296, 297, 298, 299, 300, 301, 302, 303, 304, 305, 306, 307, 308, 309, 310, 311, 312, 313, 314, 315, And 316, All Under The National Internal Revenue Code Of 1997, As Amended, And For Other Purposes </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to encourage investment by reducing the corporate income tax (CIT) rate from 30% to 20%; ensure that the grant of fiscal incentives helps bring in the greatest benefits, such as higher and more dispersed investments, more jobs, and better technology; ensure fairness and transparency in the grant of fiscal incentives; and enhance the accountability of taxpayers through more efficient tax administration.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : Corporate Income Tax and Incentives Rationalization Act  or CITIRA</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SUANSING, HORACIO JR. P., SUANSING, ESTRELLITA B., SALCEDA, JOEY SARTE, SINGSON-MEEHAN, KRISTINE, VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND &quot;LRAY&quot; JR F., CUA, JUNIE E., GARIN, SHARON S., GONZALES, AURELIO &quot;DONG&quot; JR. D., ROMERO, MICHAEL ODYLON L., HOFER, ANN K., RODRIGUEZ, RUFUS B., UNGAB, ISIDRO T., VIOLAGO, MICAELA S., TAN, ALYSSA SHEENA P., SUAREZ, ALETA C., YAP, ERIC G., 